<script type="text/javascript">
    function loadVideo(guid, playlist) {
        videojs(guid, playlist, function () {
            var origWidth = jQuery('#' + guid).parent().data('width');
            var origHeight = jQuery('#' + guid).parent().data('height');

            var actualWidth = jQuery('#' + guid).parent().width();
            if (origWidth > actualWidth) {
                this.height(origHeight * (actualWidth / origWidth));
                this.width(actualWidth);

                //Retroactively fixes an issue with resizing videos
                //the style attribute shouldn't be on the parent
                jQuery('#' + guid).parent().removeAttr('style');

            } else {
                this.height(origHeight);
                this.width(origWidth);
            }
            if (playlist != '{}') {
                this.on('ended', function () {
                    this.playlist.next();
                });
            }

            //fixes issue in IE when going full screen
            //video would be behind other content on the page
            this.on('enterFullWindow', function () {
                $(this.el).parents().not('html,body').each(function () {
                    $(this)
                        .data('oldzindex', $(this).css('z-index'))
                        .css('z-index', 99999)
                        .addClass('forcedzindex');
                });
            });
            this.on('exitFullWindow', function () {
                $('.forcedzindex').each(function () {
                    $(this)
                        .css('z-index', $(this).data('oldzindex'))
                        .removeClass('forcedzindex')
                        .removeData('oldzindex');
                });

            });
        });
    }

<script>

    if (!Array.prototype.indexOf)
        Array.prototype.indexOf = function (searchValue, index) {
            // In non-strict-mode, if the `this` variable is null
            // or undefined, then it is set the the window object.
            // Else, `this` is automaticly converted to an object.
            var len = this.length >>> 0; // convert ot number or 0

            index |= 0;              // rounds and NaN-checks
            if (index < 0)             // check if negative start
                index = Math.max(len - index, 0);
            else if (index >= len) // else, check if too big
                return -1;

            if (searchValue === undefined)
                // Because searchValue is undefined, keys that
                // don't exist will have the same value as the
                // searchValue, and thus do need to be checked.
                do {
                    if (index in this && this[index] === undefined)
                        return index;
                } while (++index !== len)
            else
                // Because searchValue is not undefined, there's no
                // need to check if the current key is in the array
                // because if the key isn't in the array, then it's
                // undefined which is not equal to the searchValue.
                do {
                    if (this[index] === searchValue)
                        return index;
                } while (++index !== len)

            // if nothing was found, then simply return -1
            return -1;
        };

				var style;

									for (var i = 0, l = style.length; i < l; i++) {
										name = style[i];
										camel = camelize(name);
										value = style.getPropertyValue(name);
										product[camel] = value;
									}
								} else {
									// opera
									for (name in style) {
										camel = camelize(name);
										value = style.getPropertyValue(name) || style[name];
										product[camel] = value;
									}
								}
							}
						}
						// IE - first try currentStyle, then normal style object - don't bother with runtimeStyle
						else if (style = dom.currentStyle) {
							for (name in style) {
								product[name] = style[name];
							}
						}
						else if (style = dom.style) {
							for (name in style) {
								if (typeof style[name] != 'function') {
									product[name] = style[name];
								}
							}
						}
					}
				}

				// remove any styles specified...
				// be careful on blacklist - sometimes vendor-specific values aren't obvious but will be visible...  e.g., excepting 'color' will still let '-webkit-text-fill-color' through, which will in fact color the text
				if (except && except instanceof Array) {
					for (var i = 0, l = except.length; i < l; i++) {
						name = except[i];
						delete product[name];
					}
				}

				// one way out so we can process blacklist in one spot
				return product;

			};

			// sugar - source is the selector, dom element or jQuery instance to copy from - only and except are optional
			$.fn.copyCSS = function (source, only, except) {
				var styles = $(source).getStyles(only, except);
				this.css(styles);

				return this;
			};
		})(jQuery);

		var expanded = false;

		$(window).load(function () {
			$('#newsTickerContent').copyCSS('#newsTicker .tickerItem', ['color', 'background-color']);
			$('#newsTickerContent').copyCSS('#newsTicker', ['background-color']);
			$('#expandTicker').copyCSS('#newsTicker .tickerItem', ['color']);
		});

		$('#expandTicker').click(function () {
			if (expanded) {
				$('#newsTicker').addClass('tickerImpShow').removeClass('tickerImpHide');
				$('#newsTickerContent').addClass('tickerImpHide').removeClass('tickerImpShow');
				expanded = false;
			}
			else {
				$('#newsTicker').addClass('tickerImpHide').removeClass('tickerImpShow');
				$('#newsTickerContent').addClass('tickerImpShow').removeClass('tickerImpHide');
				expanded = true;
			}
		});

		$(function () {
			var items = $('#newsTickerContent li');
			var index = 0;
			var tickerTimeout = null;
			var paused = false;

			tickerCycle();

			$('#newsTicker').hover(function () {
				paused = true;
				if (tickerTimeout) {
					window.clearTimeout(tickerTimeout);
					tickerTimeout = null;
				}
			}, function () {
				if (paused && !tickerTimeout) {
					tickerTimeout = window.setTimeout(function () {
						paused = false;
						tickerCycle();
					}, 3000);
				}
			});

			function tickerCycle() {
				var target = $('#newsTickerInner');
				var startOffset = 1024;
				var item = items[index];
				if (++index >= items.length) index = 0;

				removeCurrentTickerItem(function () {
					var tickerItemWrapper = $("<div>")
						.addClass("tickerItemWrapper")
						.css('left', startOffset + 'px');
					$("<div>")
						.addClass("tickerItem")
						.html($(item).html())
						.appendTo(tickerItemWrapper);
					$(tickerItemWrapper).appendTo(target);

					var targetOffset = '0px';
					$(tickerItemWrapper).animate({ left: targetOffset }, 1500, 'easeOutCirc', function () {
						if (!paused) {
							tickerTimeout = window.setTimeout(function () {
								tickerCycle();
								tickerTimeout = null;
							}, 3000);
						}
					});
				});
			}

			function removeCurrentTickerItem(callback) {
				if ($('#newsTickerInner .tickerItemWrapper').length > 0) {
					var targetOffset = '-1024px';
					$('#newsTickerInner .tickerItemWrapper').animate({ left: targetOffset }, 1500, 'easeOutCirc', function () {
						$(this).remove();
					});
					callback();
				} else {
					callback();
				}
			}
		});
	</script>

</div>

			</div>
		</div>
